<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Clinches Dutch-Sponsored Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe International
Book Fair (ZIBF) was awarded the first prize of 100,000 U.S.
Dollars in the Prince Claus awards for its contribution to the
development of African literature and culture.
</P>
<P>
ZIBF came first among other organizations in the awards that
are sponsored by the Prince Claus Fund of the Netherlands, the
Zimbabwe News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Prince Claus Fund promotes and supports activities in the
fields of culture and development.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the awards organizers in the Netherlands
today said, ''the ZIBF shows great enthusiasm and commitment,
and strives to open up new horizons and cross borders. It is also
awarded the prize because of its powerful stimulation of the
African continent's literary and cultural development, and
unconventional activities.''
</P>
<P>
The ZIBF has in recent years become the biggest annual trade
fair for African literature and an important meeting place for
African publishers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
