<HEADLINE> UNICEF Grants Aid for Children's Program in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Children's Fund (UNICEF) has agreed to provide an assistance of
53.4 million U.S. dollars for implementing a program of
cooperation in Nepal in the period of 1997-2001, Nepal's official
RSS news agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The program intends to help reduce maternal and child
mortality, improve sanitation and hygiene practices, improve
nutrition and ensure child development through providing a quality
learning environment and equal learning opportunities for girls
and for children with special needs, and encourage shared rights
and responsibilities between men and women, the RSS said.
</P>
</TEXT>
