<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Duma Approves General Pardon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW. December 24 (Xinhua) -- Russia's State Duma, the
parliament, passed a resolution Wednesday on a conditional general
amnesty for prisoners, media reports said.
</P>
<P>
Under the resolution passed in a vote 362 to 9, about 400,000
prisoners will benefit from the pardon, of whom 35,000 will be
released.
</P>
<P>
Those to be released will include the prisoners who have
reached the retirement age, served in the armed forces, joined in
the battles defending the country, won national medals, or become
handicapped or suffered from pulmonary tuberculosis.
</P>
<P>
The remaining jail terms of those who pose no serious threat to
public security will be cut by one-third.
</P>
<P>
The pardon, however, does not apply to malfeasants, murderers,
spies, terrorists and traitors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
