<HEADLINE> Chinese President Says Stability Is of "Utmost Importance" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
called on the country's law enforcement departments to make
continuous efforts to maintain social stability, saying that
stability is of "utmost importance."
</P>
<P>
Addressing a national law enforcement conference which ended
here today, Jiang, also general secretary of the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China, analysed the international and
domestic situations.
</P>
<P>
"The domestic situation as a whole is good," he said. "We must
fully use all favourable conditions and give full play to all of
our advantages to achieve new victory in reform, development and
stability."
</P>
<P>
"The foundation for maintaining social and political stability
is concentrating on developing our economy and steadily improving
people's life," he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
"Stability is the prerequisite for reform and development," he
noted, adding, "Without stability, we would achieve nothing and
would forfeit what we have achieved."
</P>
<P>
"The Party committees and governments at all levels,
particularly the number one man in the leadership, must shoulder
the political responsibility for maintaining stability," he
stressed.
</P>
<P>
"As the special force of maintaining social stability, the
country's law enforcement departments must continue to give top
priority to maintaining social stability," he said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking about maintaining public security, Jiang pointed out
that public security is of immediate concern to the life and
property of the people, to the stable environment of reform,
opening up and the modernization drive and to the international
image of China.
</P>
<P>
"Maintaining a good public order needs the common efforts of
the whole Party and the whole society," he said. Jiang also
stressed the necessity of seriously cracking down on grave
criminal activities, saying, "Cracking down on serious crimes is
an important link in comprehensively improving public order."
</P>
<P>
All law enforcement departments must take all kinds of
appropriate measures to crack down on grave criminal activities
which severely jeopardize public security and endanger people's
life and property, he said.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, the Chinese president also pointed out the
corruption within the country's law enforcement departments.
</P>
<P>
"Corruption such as taking bribes and bending the law or
bullying and oppressing the people has seriously tarnished the
image of our law enforcement departments and hurt the prestige of
our Party and the government," he warned.
</P>
<P>
"Those people who abuse their power or pervert justice for a
bribe must be expelled from the law enforcement departments
relentlessly," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang stressed three aspects in future work: to continue to
strengthen legislature, to ensure that government departments do
administrative work according to law and to make sure that law
enforcement departments strictly enforce the law.
</P>
<P>
Chinese premier Li Peng also gave a speech at today's
meeting. He emphasized that the political and professional quality
of people working in the law enforcement departments should be
improved continuously.
</P>
<P>
He said more efforts will be made on enterprise reform and
government restructuring next year, and hence social stability is
all the more important for the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
