<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Britain Hit by Storm on Christmas Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 25 (Xinhua) -- A strong gale and heavy rain
hit Britain today, leaving at least two people dead and thousands
without electricity on Christmas Day.
</P>
<P>
The storm from the Atlantic Ocean downed trees, snapped power
lines and ripped tiles from roofs, reports said.
</P>
<P>
North Wales and northern England were the worst hit with dozens
of roads blocked by hundreds of fallen trees.
</P>
<P>
The two deaths occurred in separate road accidents in
northwestern England, police said. A woman was killed when a large
tree fell on her car, and a second woman died in a multiple car
pile-up that resulted from storm-related circumstances.
</P>
<P>
Police and motoring organizations across Britain were warning
people not to drive today unless the journey was absolutely
necessary. Torrential rains made driving difficult, and more high
winds were expected in the south and west of England later in the
day.
</P>
<P>
Authorities said 35,000 homes lost power in the overnight storm
in northwestern England and Wales, although power crews had
restored service to some of them by midday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
