<HEADLINE> Disaster Relief Goods Arrives in Snowstorm-Hit Tibetan Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAGQU, December 25 (Xinhua) -- The snowstorm-hit Nagqu
Prefecture in the northern Tibet Autonomous Region has received
1.92 million yuan (about 240,000 US dollars) of disaster relief
fund from the regional government, along with food, clothes and
fuels donated by people and units from all parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Some 150,000 kg of grain, 3000 pieces of clothes and large
quantity of fuels, including 500 tons of coal, 300,000 liters of
diesel oil and gasoline have arrived in the area.
</P>
<P>
Heavy snowfalls have caused serious difficulties in the
prefecture since early this month, but no deaths of people were
reported thanks to the government's disaster relief effort.
</P>
<P>
About 260,000 people and five million heads of livestocks are
suffering from the disaster in 110 townships, where the snowfall
is 40 cm on average. In some heavily-hit villages, the snowfall
has reached above 50 cm.
</P>
<P>
The first group of disaster relief goods have already been
distributed to the local victims.  
</P>
</TEXT>
