<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian State Duma Passes 1998 Budget in Second Reading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Russian State Duma (the Lower
House) on Thursday endorsed the long-disputed federal budget for
1998 in the second reading with a vote of 231 to 155.
</P>
<P>
According to the Interfax news agency, the budget bill requires
a minimum of 226 votes for passage in a reading and the Duma has
to approve it in four readings before its submission to the Upper
House and the president for final approval.
</P>
<P>
The basic budget expenditures that have gained legal
endorsement total 499.9 billion re-denominated rubles.
</P>
<P>
The third reading of the budget is scheduled to open on January
23. Prior to that, the amendments to the budget are required to be
submitted to the Budget Committee no later than January 10.
</P>
<P>
The Duma failed to approve the budget bill in the second
reading on Wednesday for the lack of just one vote.
</P>
<P>
The State Duma passed the 1998 budget draft bill in first
reading on December 5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
