<HEADLINE> China to Start New Charge System on Int'l Calls beginning from New Year's Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- International calls made at
night, on week-ends and public holidays will be charged less than
in other time starting January 1, 1998, according to new
regulations issued by China's Ministry of Posts and
Telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
According to the regulations, calls made from 07:00 to 21:00
from Monday to Friday (excluding on public holidays) will be
charged with standard fees; those from 21:00 to 24:00 from Monday
to Friday, and from 07:00 to 24:00 on Saturday, Sunday and public
holidays charged with 80 percent of the standard fees; and those
from 00:00 to 07:00 charged with 60 percent of the standard fees.
</P>
<P>
However, public phones, mobile phones, toll phones,
international roaming services, 200 card, 300 card, IC card and
magnetic card services, and collect calls to China are not within
the scope of the new regulations, nor are calls made to Hong Kong,
Macao and Taiwan region.  
</P>
</TEXT>
