<HEADLINE> Jiangxi Aims to Bring in 800 Million US Dollars Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, December 25 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangxi province
aims to bring in 800 million US dollars in overseas investment next
year, which will be 20 percent more than that of this year.
</P>
<P>
The province will select a group of projects with high economic
returns and competitiveness to attract overseas investors, Governor
Shu Shengyou told a provincial economic work conference which ended
here today.
</P>
<P>
The governor said that Jiangxi will designate 20 to 30 major
projects to draw the participation of transnationals and consortia
in improving its state-owned enterprises, while infrastructure,
agriculture, animal husbandry and tourism will also be the main
fields for overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
By the beginning of this month, Jiangxi has approved 429
overseas-funded projects and used 569 million US dollars of
overseas investment. The amount is expected to reach 650 million
US dollars by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
A less developed province in the prosperous east China region,
Jiangxi has seen the improvement of its investment environment
thanks to the implementation of the strategy of developing the
Yangtze basin and the going into operation of the Beijing-Kowloon
railway, a north-south rail trunk running through Jiangxi.
</P>
<P>
There are currently 5,320 overseas-funded projects in operation
in Jiangxi, with the committed overseas investment at 5.277
billion US dollars and the actual amount used at 2.28 billion.
</P>
</TEXT>
