<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Encourages People to Buy and Read More Books </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- China has carried out a
national cultural drive to encourage families and individuals to
read more books.
</P>
<P>
Xu Wenbo, deputy Culture Minister, said at a work conference
here today that the drive is aimed at promoting the collecting and
reading of good books among the citizens and further improving
their quality.
</P>
<P>
The drive started in January this year, and has so far set up
32,600 public reading rooms in libraries and cultural centers
across the country, according to Xu.
</P>
<P>
Up to date, more than 18 million readers has attended a variety
of reading activities organized by cultural and educational
departments at all levels, he said.
</P>
<P>
Xu also urged publishing houses and book stores nationwide to
provide more and better publications for readers. 
</P>
