<HEADLINE> Quakes Hit Bangladeshi Port City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Two mild earthquakes jolted the
port city of Chittagong, 224 kilometers southeast of Dhaka, and
its adjacent areas on Thursday morning, the Bangladesh Seismic
Observation Center said.
</P>
<P>
The first tremor took place at 7:23:02 a.m. (Local time) and
lasted for 12 seconds, and the epicenter was located at 101
kilometers off the port.
</P>
<P>
Some residents felt the tremor but most of the people were
asleep and did not feel it.
</P>
<P>
The second quake which started jolting at 7:24:20 a.m., lasted
for about 14 seconds, and its epicenter was located at 125
kilometers off the port.
</P>
<P>
Richter scale of the tremors was not clear, and no report on
any casualty was available.  
</P>
