the country have been agitating since December 4 to seek parity in
wages, allowances and perks with their counterparts in the
national division.
</P>
<P>
The Airports Authority of India management is in the process of
sorting out differences in pay, perks and status of its employees
arising out of the merger of the international and national
airports divisions into it last year.  
