<HEADLINE> Works of Modern French Writer Translated into Arabic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 25 (Xinhua) -- The works of the modern French
writer and playwright Marcel Pagnol have been translated into Arabic
for the first time and recently published by the Dar Sharkiat
publishing house of Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The autobiographical works of Pagnol, including "La Gloire de
Mon Pere (The Glory of My Father)," "Le Chateau de Ma Mere (The
Castle of My Mother)," "Le Temps des Secrets (Times of Secret),"
and "Temps des Amours (Times of Love)," which tell about the
author's childhood in southeast France, were translated by Egyptian
Mohammad Seif.
</P>
<P>
Pagnol, who was born in 1895 and died in 1974, was also the
author of the drama trilogy "Fanny," "Marius" and "Cesar,"
which used the Old Port of the Mediterranean metropolis of Marseille
in the 1930s as its background. 
</P>
</TEXT>
