<HEADLINE> Pakistan Minister Orders Immediate Rescue Measures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Minister for
Railways Muhammad Yaqub Thursday ordered immediate rescue and
relief measures for the victims in the tragedy of train collision.
</P>
<P>
The accident happened at around 9 p.m. Wednesday when passenger
trains collided head on at the Rustam Sargana railway station,
about 240 kilometers south of Islamabad.
</P>
<P>
According to sources from the railway authority, at least 35
people were killed so far and 60 others injured, among which
several are in a very serious condition.
</P>
<P>
Yaqub directed the Railway officials to rush to the spot and
ensure special arrangements for transportation of the relatives of
the unfortunate dead to the spot.
</P>
<P>
He further directed that all possible medical facilities be
provided to those injured in the collision.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the collision occurred due to the fault of
the pointsman. A full investigation of the accident is under way.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
