<HEADLINE> Shop Robbed on Christmas Eve in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Three men wearing hood and waving
pistols rushed into a department store in Kingersheim in Haut-Rhin,
eastern France, on the Christmas Eve Wednesday evening, taking away
an unspecified amount of money.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse (AFP) quoted police as saying that the three
men forced their way into the Decathlon department store when one of
its employees opened the door for leaving the store, which was
already closed.
</P>
<P>
They forced all the remaining employees to lie on the ground and
ordered their head to open the cash box before running away with the
money in it, said police. 
</P>
