<HEADLINE> Turkish PM to Visit Turkmenistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Prime Minister Mesut
Yilmaz will pay a three-day official visit to Turkmenistan, the
world's second largest natural gas producer, at the invitation of
Turkmen President Saparmurat Atayevich Niyazov.
</P>
<P>
Local newspaper Daily News today quoted State Minister Ahat
Andican as saying "the visit by the Turkish prime minister has
multi-dimensional targets from energy to culture."
</P>
<P>
During the visit on December 26-28, a decision will probably be
made on the route to carry Turkmen gas to Turkey, he said.
</P>
<P>
"An under-Caspian pipeline and a pipeline via Iran are two
options. The feasibility study for the Caspian option has been
completed, while that of the Iranian route is still continuing,"
Andican said.
</P>
<P>
"The legal status of the Caspian Sea is a major problem for the
Caspian option, while the Iranian route entails different
problems," he added.
</P>
<P>
Andican pointed out that Turkey's growing natural gas needs
will reach 70 billion cubic meters in the first decades of the
next century.
</P>
<P>
During Yilmaz's visit, Turkey and Turkmenistan will sign
agreements in the areas of health, tourism and culture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
