<HEADLINE> Exports of Central China Province Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 25 (Xinhua) -- The trade volume of
central-south China's Hunan Province registered a rise of 13.98
percent in the first 11 months of this year at 2.95 billion US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Export of foreign-funded enterprises totalled 496 million US
dollars, representing a 91-percent increase compared with last
year's same period
</P>
<P>
The province exported 581 million U.S. dollar-worth of products
to Hong Kong and Macao in the first 11 months, accounting for more
than one quarter of its total export.
</P>
<P>
Major exports were farm produce and textile goods, said a
provincial trade official.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Hunan Province has increased its export to Japan,
Singapore and the United States this year.
</P>
<P>
The province's export to the the US in the first 11 months
totalled 201 million U.S. dollars, 38 million dollars more than
that in the corresponding period a year ago.  
</P>
