<HEADLINE> 16 Killed in Fighting in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 25 (Xinhua) -- At least 16 people were killed
Wednesday in the fighting between the Sri Lankan government troops
and Tamil rebels in Kilinochchi, Northern Province, a military
spokesman said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said around 13 rebels were killed in the
crossfire. One officer and two soldiers were also killed and six
others injured during the confrontation.
</P>
<P>
There have been sporadic fighting between the two sides since
the troops launched an offensive in May to open a land route
connecting the frontier town of Vavuniya with Kilinochchi.
</P>
<P>
The Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam has been fighting for a
separate state of their own in the north and east of the island
country since 1983. The government says about 55,000 people have
been killed in the ethnic war.  
</P>
