<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Meets Tax Revenue Target Ahead of Schedule </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- China collected more than
707.1 billion yuan (about 85.2 billion US dollars) in industrial
and commercial taxes by 20 this month, fulfilling its tax revenue
budget this year 11 days ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
The total amount, which was 17.8 percent more than a year ago,
represented 101.7 percent of this year's target, the State
Administration of Taxation (SAT) said.
</P>
<P>
However, collection of the value-added tax and the consumption
tax, two major tax items under China's new tax regime introduced
in 1994, was not satisfactory, the SAT said.
</P>
<P>
The revenue of the two major taxes totaled 377.6 billion yuan
by December 20, up 11.2 percent year-on-year or 92.3 percent of
the targeted figure for this year.
</P>
<P>
An analysis shows that Hebei Province, the special economic
zone of Shenzhen, and the Tibet and Ningxia Hui autonomous regions
have overfulfilled their yearly targets.
</P>
<P>
The SAT urged tax agencies at all levels to make greater
efforts to collect delayed taxes in the last few days of the
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971225.0082 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Progress Reported in Sino-Foreign Agricultural Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- China achieved marked progress
in expanding agricultural cooperation with other countries this
year, an agricultural official said here today.
</P>
<P>
The country has set up joint agricultural committees with
Thailand, Guinea, Egypt, the Netherlands and Russia and signed
agricultural agreements with more than 20 countries, said
Gan Zuofu, deputy director of the International Cooperation
Department under the Ministry of Agriculture, in an interview with
Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
China also joined hands with the World Bank, Asian Development
Bank and United Nations Food and Agriculture Organization in
carrying out a wide range of agricultural and scientific
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
China this year has imported more than 100,000 strains of
grain, cotton, fruit and vegetable as well as poultry breeds. It
sent 6,000 students and visiting scholars to study in other
countries and invited 1,000 agro-scientists to offer technical
support in China, Gan said.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture this year has brought in 120
million U.S. dollars from abroad to develop agriculture. Some of
the funds has been used in comprehensive agricultural development
in poverty-stricken areas in Qinghai and Gansu provinces.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands has invested 5 million U.S. dollars in building
a pilot pig farm in Beijing and a horticulture center in
Shanghai. Both began operations in the last half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China has sent 58 agricultural experts to help
Guinea build a 400-hectare grain base. The first phase of the
project has been completed with each hectare producing 5.8 tons of
grain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
