<HEADLINE> Jilin to Boost Environmental Protection Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Jilin
Province, a leading industrial base, decided to foster its
environment business as one of its future pillar industries.
</P>
<P>
Jilin recently announced its 12-year development plan for
environment protection industry, which is expected to become one
of its pillar industries.
</P>
<P>
The province is in an urgent need of boosting the manufacture
of industrial and domestic waste sewage disposal equipment, air
pollution control equipment, domestic garbage disposal facilities,
water-saving facilities and environment monitoring instrument.
</P>
<P>
The automobile, pharmaceutical and chemical industries, and
forestry are the province's pillar industries and Jilin is also
one of the country's largest commodity grain producers.
</P>
<P>
In an effort to spur the growth of the environmental protection
industry, Jilin allows the environmental protection department to
use five to eight percent of the fees collected from waste
discharge for development of new technology, new equipment, new
materials and demonstration projects of environmental protection.
 
</P>
