<HEADLINE> East China Province Receiving over 50 Million Tourists in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province
has received more than 50 million tourists this year, including
one million tourists from overseas.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that Jiangsu will have witnessed a rise of 17.2
percent this year over 1996 in term of the number of overseas
tourist arrivals, and will earn 390 million U.S. dollars from
overseas tourism services, an increase of 23 percent over 1996,
said Lu Sujie, director of the Jiangsu Provincial Tourism
Administration.
</P>
<P>
According to the director, the province has so far received
52.65 million domestic tourists and earned 36.4 billion yuan (4.39
billion US dollars) from the related services.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu abounds in natural resources and has 91 of the 740 most
popular tourist sites in China that have been listed by the
National Tourism Administration, ranking the first among all
provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions of the country.
</P>
