According to latest reports, death toll in the tragedy of train
collision at Rustam Sargana, about 240 km south of Pakistan's
capital, Wednesday night, rose to 34.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 60 injured who have been shifted to hospitals in
nearby cities, several are in a very serious condition.
</P>
<P>
As the rescue operation continued on Thursday amidst fog and
rain, the death toll is feared to rise further.
</P>
<P>
Due to inclement weather, the rescue operation teams were
facing difficulties in their task.  
