<HEADLINE> Hunan Starts Afforestation Project around Dongting Lake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 25 (Xinhua) -- An afforestation project
funded jointly by China and Germany around the Dongting Lake, the
second largest freshwater lake in China, is now under way in
central-south China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
With an aim to improve the ecological environment around the
lake and the middle reaches of the Yangtze River, the project is
expected to cover eight cities and counties including Yueyang,
Linxiang, Yunxi, Huarong, Nanxian, Anhua, Lixian and Jinshi.
</P>
<P>
The five-year project involves the afforesting of 30,000
hectares, including 7,000 hectares by lake dam sites for flood
control and 16,000 hectares on mountainsides for erosion control.
</P>
<P>
According to the Hunan Provincial Government, the total
investment to the project is 94.33 million yuan (11.37 million US
dollars) with 63.6 percent deriving from Germany and the remainder
from the eight cities and counties around the lake as well as
Hunnan province.
</P>
<P>
A provincial government official said that the project will
help farmers in the region around the Dongting Lake to increase
their income by undertaking irrigation projects and opening up
hilly lands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
