<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Becomes Experimental City for Technology Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 25 (Xinhua) -- China's State Science and
Technology Commission (SSTC) has approved Tianjin as one of the
country's five experimental cities for technology export.
</P>
<P>
An official of this north China municipal government said that
Tianjin's export volume has increased by 20 percent with a goal of
180 million U.S. dollars for 1997. SSTC will support Tianjin with
loans, information and personnel training.
</P>
<P>
Centering on the chemical industry, 20 projects with an annual
export volume of over one million U.S. dollars each will be set up
as examples for others to follow.
</P>
<P>
With regard to pillar industries such as automotive, machinery,
electricity, chemicals and metallurgy, 20 high-tech enterprises
with an annual export volume of more than one million U.S. dollars
will be chosen to be leaders in technology export development.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Tianjin municipality will support six-to-eight
enterprises with obvious achievements in technology export. And
priority also will be given to trade companies with an annual
export volume exceeding five million U.S. dollars to encourage
trade development.
</P>
<P>
While reinforcing Southeast Asian and African markets, the
Tianjin municipal government also will strive to develop East
European and Latin American markets.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971225.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Round-up: S. African Tourism Developing Fast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Tourism in South Africa
has been developing in leaps and bounds since the abolition of
apartheid in 1994 that makes it possible for Pretoria to return
to the world community, paving the way for the promotion of the
industry.
</P>
<P>
According to Tourism Minister Pallo Jordan, the number of
overseas visitors to the country increased by 1.26 million in
1995 compared with 1994, recording a 34.8 percent increase. And
in 1996, almost five million tourists visited South Africa and
the projected figure for 2000 is about 7.5 million.
</P>
<P>
The higher number of tourists brought in an estimated increase
of 7.5 billion Rands (1.7 billion Dollars) in 1995, a 107 percent
growth in foreign exchange as against 1994, Jordan noted.
</P>
<P>
Last year, South African tourism has earned 5.7 billion U.S.
Dollars, with 37,000 direct and 74,000 indirect job opportunities
having been created, he said, adding that one direct and two
indirect job opportunities would be created by each 33 additional
visitors.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the minister said, in accordance with the current
growth rate, tourism contribution to the country's GDP could rise
from the present 4.5 percent to 10 percent, generating 40 billion
Rand (8.5 billion U.S. Dollars) annually and creating two million
jobs.
</P>
<P>
"No other industry has such potential," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Tourism is a powerful engine for job-creation, economic
revival and will generate much-needed foreign currency," said
President Nelson Mandela.
</P>
<P>
South Africa is well known for its exceptional tourism
advantages: the magnificent panorama of Cape of Good Hope, the
world-renowned Kruger National Park which stretches about 20,000
square kilometers, and diverse folk cultures...
</P>
<P>
What is more, well accommodated and good serviced hotels,
well-netted air and road traffic, which are not at all inferior
to their European counterparts, have turned South Africa into the
most favored tourist resort in African continent.
</P>
<P>
South Africa, also famous for its gold and diamond production,
could not give a full play to its tourism advantages due to the
implementation of inhumane apartheid before 1994. During that
period, South Africa was even below the average world level in
terms of tourism income against population ratio, let alone to be
a tourism giant.
</P>
<P>
Cape Town, the legislative capital of South Africa, is the
most important tourist destination in the country. It is also
listed as one of 10 famous resorts in the world.
</P>
<P>
Although it failed to win the bid to host the 2004 Olympic
Games, Cape Town, known as the Mother City, has after all made a
very successful advertisement for itself both at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
Upon the eve of Christmas and the annual festive season, all
the hotels and scenic spots in the city have been filled with
travelers pouring in from all directions.
</P>
<P>
Facing the increasing tourists, the Cape Town municipal
government pledged that they would do their best to improve
travel services in line with the latest international standard.
</P>
<P>
In addition, city officials have also expressed determination
to maintain good relations and cooperation between the black and
the white so as to create better environment for tourism.
</P>
<P>
Following the example of Capetonian counterparts, many travel
agencies and groups in other parts of South Africa are extending
and polishing travel facilities.
</P>
<P>
The development of tourism in South Africa has played an
active part in promoting tourism in the whole African continent.
So far hotel chain groups in more than 13 African countries have
made investments in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Experts in the industry said tourism, which can be one of the
most powerful engines of an African renaissance, is becoming a
major driving force behind economic growth in Africa, and is
expected to create another three million jobs by 2000.
</P>
<P>
As China and South Africa establish comprehensive diplomatic
relations at the end of this year, some South African travel
agencies and hotel groups have also started seeking ways to
extend cooperation with their Chinese counterparts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
