<HEADLINE> Hainan Province Expecting Record Agricultural Harvests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Hainan, an island province in
south China, is expecting to harvest a record 2.17 million tons of
grain this year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it expects to produce 2.1 million tons of
vegetables, 450,000 tons of fruit, 515,000 tons of aquatic
products and 260,000 tons of rubber. Output of all these products
could set new records.
</P>
<P>
The industrial output value of township-run enterprises
recorded double-digit growth to reach 8.4 billion yuan this year.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the per capita net income of rural residents is
expected to reach 2,000 yuan. More than 160,000 rural residents
living below the poverty line (annual income of less than 500
yuan) have improved their living standards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
