<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Airline Resumes Domestic Flight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 25 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladesh national airline,
Biman, will resume partially its domestic flights on Thursday, the
local press reported.
</P>
<P>
A flight linking Dhaka and Chittagong would start at 11:40 a.m.
(local time) and land at 2:50 p.m., the first domestic flight
since an F-28 aircraft of Biman met with an accident on Monday
night in Sylhet, 200 kilometers north of Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
The operation of domestic flights would remain limited in
Dhaka-Sylhet, Dhaka-Chittagong and Dhaka-Jessore routes only, and
flights linking Dhaka with other cities would remain closed,
according to Biman officials.
</P>
<P>
It was not possible to resume normal operation of all domestic
flights within the next three months, and at least 50 percent of
the weekly domestic flights numbering 60 would remain postponed
till January, they said.
</P>
<P>
The Biman aircraft made a near-crash landing near the Sylhet
Osmany airport Monday night, injuring 17 people, including the
pilot and three crew members.  
</P>
