<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
has called for an intensified crackdown on economic malpractice in an
effort to create a fairer environment for market competition in
China.
</P>
<P>
He also called for intensified efforts to enact more and
improved laws and regulations guiding the operation of the market
economy.
</P>
<P>
The leader made his remarks after listening to a report
on the work of the State Administration for Industry and Commerce
(SAIC) which serves as the market watchdog.
</P>
<P>
He said the industry and commerce departments are important for
enforcing laws and regulations by administrative means under
socialist market-economy conditions. Its role in the present
period cannot be under-estimated, he said.
</P>
<P>
"To ensure the market economy develops in a sound and orderly
way, we should have an authoritative department to maintain the
fair market order, and that role mainly goes to the industry and
commerce departments," he said.
</P>
<P>
Li praised the market watchdogs for their achievements in
recent years in cracking down on the production and sale of fake
and shoddy goods, smuggling, cheating through contracts and
illegal pyramid selling.
</P>
<P>
"The tens of thousands of industry and commerce personnel
working across the country are an indispensable force in
maintaining the market economic order. They should constantly
improve their political awareness, professional skills
and work style," he urged.
</P>
<P>
The vice premier's remarks were made during a three-day
national work conference on industry and commerce which closed
here today.
</P>
<P>
In a report delivered on the conference, Wang Zhongfu, SAIC's
director-general, called for intensified crackdowns on the
production and sale of fake and shoddy goods, pornographic and
illegal publications, smuggling and drugs. 
