<HEADLINE> Fossil Stratum in Yunnan Province of China Protected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- The area where the Chengjiang
Arthropod Fossil Stratum is discovered has been well protected in
southwest China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
According to regulations issued by the provincial government,
no one is allowed to enter the area without permission and that no
tourist and production activities can be conducted around the
area.
</P>
<P>
The Arthropod Fossil Stratum, located in Chengjiang county and
dating back some 500 million years, was first discovered in
1981. It contains a big quantity of fossils of over 100 varieties
of different animals.
</P>
<P>
Regarded as one of the most valuable evidences in
speciation, the stratum has been subscribed on UNESCO's World
Heritage List. 
</P>
