<HEADLINE> Labor Skills Foundation Established in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- The State Education Commission
(SEC) and Huamao Group, the largest Chinese producer of teaching
apparatus, jointly established the Labor Education Foundation for
primary and secondary schools in Beijing on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ningbo Huamao Group, a enterprise based in the port city of
Ningbo in Zhejiang Province, donated three million yuan ($375,000
U.S. dollars) to the SEC to fund the project, as well as
laboratory instruments worth three million yuan to improve
teaching conditions in primary and secondary schools in
poverty-stricken areas in China.
</P>
<P>
According to an SEC official, establishing the foundation will
aid the development of labor skills and award outstanding
individuals in education.
</P>
<P>
Huamao Group, China's largest educational research and
production center, has donated 35 million yuan ($4.75 million
U.S. dollars) to set up foundations on nature education,
technology and labor skills since 1992.
</P>
<P>
Work skills education is aimed at improving students' manual
dexterity and enriching their knowledge of technology.
</P>
<P>
This project is a concrete step taken by the SEC to challenge
examination-oriented education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
