<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fourth Collection of Chinese Literature Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 25 (Xinhua) -- The fourth collection of new
Chinese literature (1949-1976) has been published by Shanghai
Literature and Art Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
The fourth collection includes 20 volumes covering literary
theories, fictions, dramas, films, essays, poetries and historical
materials. Literary works during the 1949-1976 period by writers
from Taiwan, Hong Kong and Macao were also included in the
collection for the first time.
</P>
<P>
The first collection (1917-1927) was compiled in the 1930s and
published in the 1980s. Later, the Shanghai Literature and Art
Publishing House published the second 20-volume collection
(1927-1937) and the third 20-volume collection (1937-1949).
</P>
<P>
Xinhua learned that the Shanghai Literature and Art Publishing
House has started work on the fifth collection which will cover
literary achievements during the 1976-2000 period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
