<HEADLINE> Drama Staged on Life of 10th Panchen Lama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- The first performance of a
modern drama on the life of the 10th Panchen Lama was staged
Wednesday in Xining, capital of northwest China's Qinghai Province.
</P>
<P>
Panchen Erdini Qoigyi Gyaincian (1938-1989), a native of
Qinghai, was one of the two chief lamas of the Gelupa (yellow
sect) of Tibetan Buddhism. He was officially recognized as the
10th Panchen on June 3, 1949.
</P>
<P>
The 10th Panchen, a patriotic religious leader, contributed
greatly to the unity of China's ethnic groups and to political
stability. "We want to show his brilliant life to the public
through this play," said Wang Nian, the playwright.
</P>
<P>
The actors visited the panchen's mother, relatives and friends
in a bid to have a better understanding of his life, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
The play will be shown around the province from now to the
Spring Festival, and then will be staged in Beijing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
