<HEADLINE> Thai Police Step up Crackdown on Social Vices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Thai police have intensified
crackdown on drug orgies, child prostitution, theft, gun-running
and gambling during the festival season.
</P>
<P>
Starting Thursday (Christmas day), police will keep a close
watch on ex-convicts, gunmen, some infamous "influential figures"
and people who are publicly drunk.
</P>
<P>
Their focus will be on places of entertainment that are
unlicensed or that stay open beyond legal closing times.
</P>
<P>
For this purpose, special checkpoints have been set up and
police teams will patrol "risky" areas, such as department stores,
financial institutions, slums, low-grade hotels and construction
sites.
</P>
<P>
Agencies under the Bangkok Police Bureau have been requested to
make daily reports on their performance and important cases.
</P>
<P>
During the new year holiday (January 1-4), police at some
Bangkok stations will begin work earlier than usual.
</P>
<P>
The "clean-up" campaign is aimed not only at maintaining peace
around new year's day but also at improving the country's image
for the "amazing Thailand" tourism years of 1998 and 1999.
</P>
</TEXT>
