<HEADLINE> Thai Trade Deficit Expected to Drop Sharply in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's foreign trade
deficit is expected to narrow to about 620 million U.S. dollars in
1998 from an estimated 4.62 billion dollars this year, the Thai
Commerce Ministry predicts.
</P>
<P>
According to figures from the Business Economics Department
under the ministry available on Thursday, Thailand's export value
is expected to grow to 62 billion dollars in 1998, while its
import value would drop to 62.62 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
For this year, the department said, Thailand's exports are
estimated at 57.87 billion dollars, with imports at 62.49 billion
dollars.
</P>
<P>
However, Thai deputy prime minister and commerce minister
Supachai Panitchpakdi said Wednesday that Thailand has to do more
to meet the estimated targets for next year.
</P>
<P>
The government would provide funds to ease cash flow pressure
for exporters, while trying to expand the existing markets and
explore new ones, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also predicted that Thailand's economic growth could be at
zero.  
</P>
</TEXT>
