<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Urged to Push Foreign Investment Work to New High (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- China's leading newspaper,
"People's Daily," today carried an editorial urging the country to
push its use of foreign investment work to a new high.
</P>
<P>
After a national conference on utilization of foreign
investment which opened in Beijing Monday and closed Wednesday,
China is urged to open further to the outside world and continue
to make use of foreign investment in an active, rational and
efficient manner to help promote rapid and healthy growth in the
economy and overall social progress.
</P>
<P>
The editorial stressed that the conference would have
far-reaching impact on China's utilization of foreign investment
in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
According to the editorial, in less than 20 years China has
attracted more than 360 billion U.S. dollars, including 220
million U.S. dollars in direct foreign investment, to rank first
in utilizing direct foreign funding among developing nations and
second in the world.
</P>
<P>
The editorial stated that foreign-invested enterprises have
become an important part of China's socialist market
economy. Among the total assets of 240,000-plus foreign-funded
firms in operation, state-owned and collectively owned enterprises
account for 57 percent.
</P>
<P>
The editorial called on people to correctly view the nature and
role of the foreign-funded firms from the practice of China's
primary stage of socialism and from the need to develop social
productivity.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971225.0140 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Urged to Push Foreign Investment Work to New High (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China still has lots of potentials to be one of the world's key
destinations in foreign investment, the editorial said. The
country's socialist market-economy mechanism is being set up and
improved, the political situation is stable and the market
prospects are broad, which all constitute new opportunities for
the continued growth of foreign investment. Besides, the country's
potential for scientific and technological progress is great, the
renminbi value is stable, foreign exchange earnings are sufficient
and the comprehensive production cost is low.
</P>
<P>
However, the editorial warned that the level and quantity of
the country's utilization of foreign investment are still low and
leave much to be desired.
</P>
<P>
"It is still a demanding job and the use of foreign investment
should be greatly enhanced," it said.
</P>
<P>
As the utilization of foreign investment embodies the extend of
China's opening-up, the editorial said, it will have significant
impact on the sustainable development of the economy.
</P>
<P>
The editorial elaborated that the trend toward economic and
scientific globalization requires China to actively take part in
international competition and cooperation, and make better use of
domestic and foreign resources. The country also should
unswervingly adhere to the policy of attracting more foreign
investment, especially direct foreign funding.
</P>
<P>
The editorial also encouraged attracting foreign investment in
line with overall requirements of the national economy and
improving the framework of foreign-funding expenditures. It also
stressed the utilization work's "active, rational and efficient"
features.
</P>
<P>
It explained that the socialist market economy is an open
economy and China will, in line with the Deng Xiaoping Theory,
focus on upgrading the quality and efficiency of economic
development, increase the country's comprehensive strength and
international competitiveness, further expand the opening-up and
make a better use of foreign funds in a bid to help promote the
rapid and healthy growth of the national economy and overall
social progress.  
</P>
</TEXT>
