<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Controls Pollution of River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai has completed a
pollution control project on a tributary of the Suzhou River.
</P>
<P>
As one of the six tributaries of the Suzhou River in Shanghai,
the 4.9-kilometer Zhenrugang River is a pollutant source of the
Suzhou River.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 the Shanghai Municipal Government decided to invest 60
million yuan in a project to clean up the Zhenrugang River.
</P>
<P>
The project was completed in a year with the construction of
4,069 meters of flood-control walls, the dredging of 54,000 cubic
meters of sludge and the planting of trees and grass on a
20,000-square-meter area along the river.
</P>
<P>
According to the Shanghai Water Resources Department, the
dredging of the river has improved the environment along the river
and will benefit the realignment of the Suzhou River in the coming
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
