<HEADLINE> Suspected Kidnappers of Presidential Aide Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Six suspects accused of
kidnapping Colombia's presidential press secretary and a
journalist have been arrested, police said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The suspects were captured during a surprise raid Tuesday in
Rovira, 130 kilometers west of the capital, said national police
chief General Rosso Jose Serrano.
</P>
<P>
The men, all members of the Jaime Bateman Cayon rebel band, are
charged with kidnapping press secretary William Parra and RCN
radio journalist Luis Eduardo Maldonado on December 4, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Among those under arrest was John Alexander Conde, believed to
be the third in command of the rebel group, Serrano said.
</P>
<P>
The two kidnapped were released nine days later, bringing with
them a peace proposal from the 200-member band. 
</P>
