<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Becomes One of Bulgaria's 2nd Foreign Languages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, December 25 (Xinhua) -- The Bulgarian Ministry of
Education and Science announced yesterday that from next year on
students will have more options in learning foreign languages,
Chinese included.
</P>
<P>
According to local newspapers, primary school students can
choose one from English, French, German, Italian, Spanish and
Russian as their first foreign language after entering school. In
the fifth year, the students will be asked to learn a second
foreign language, Chinese, Japanese and Portuguese are on the
optional list. Thus, they will have grasped the basic knowledge
of two foreign languages when graduating from middle schools.
</P>
<P>
In Bulgaria nowadays, there is a new upsurge in learning
foreign languages. The statistics of a company specializing in
foreign language training show that in the past seven months, more
and more Bulgarian people started learning foreign languages,
among whom 70 percent are learning English. German and Greek are
two other favorite foreign languages to them. Meanwhile, the
number of people learning Chinese is also increasing.
</P>
<P>
People usually believe that foreign language learning can give
them more advantages in the intense competition of hunting for a
job. 
</P>
</TEXT>
