<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chilean Overseas Investment Surges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Chile has seen a remarkable
increase in its investments in foreign countries this year due to
the sound and stable growth in its economy, says a financial
report released by the Chilean central bank.
</P>
<P>
In the first 11 months of this year, Chilean overseas
investment reached 1.781 billion U.S. dollars, 60 percent more
than that of the whole year of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The report says about 47 percent of Chilean overseas investment
went to South American countries, followed by Caribbean countries
and North American countries which took 22 percent and 17.4
percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Having received 393 million U.S. dollars up to November this
year, Argentina is on the top of the list in obtaining Chilean
investment, followed by the United States, Uruguay and Peru.
</P>
<P>
So far, the total amount of Chilean overseas investment has
reached 5.539 billion dollars since 1975, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The report says that up to November this year, foreign
investment in Chile has reached 830 million U.S. dollars, a 27.7
percent increase over the same period of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
