<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Budgets Heavily for Earthquake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The Italian government will
allocate three trillion lire (1.7 billion U.S. dollars) next month
to rebuild the country's central Umbria and Marche regions, hit by
an earthquake in September, Italian Premier Romano Prodi said here
today.
</P>
<P>
In January, a bill will be presented to regulate how the funds
are spent, after which the reconstruction will get underway, Prodi
said in a television broadcast.
</P>
<P>
Everything possible was being done to help the earthquake
victims, he said. "In fact among the people there is a climate of
gratitude and confidence." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
