<DOCNO> XIE19971225.0161 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy's Foreign Reserves Rise to 74.3 Billion U.S. Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of Italy's overall
foreign reserves rose slightly to 129.4 trillion lire (about 74.3
billion U.S. dollars) by the end of November, the Italian Exchange
Office (UIC) said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
However, the overall surplus in the year's first 11 months was
19.1 trillion lire (10.7 billion dollars), lower than the same
period of 1996, when the figure was 25.1 trillion lire (14 billion
dollars), data released by UIC showed.
</P>
<P>
The office attributed the decrease of surplus to the outflow of
Italian capital, which amounted to 12.4 trillion lire (7 billion
dollars) in the 11-month period.
</P>
<P>
The nation's foreign debt totalled 75.6 trillion lire (43
billion dollars) by the end of November. 
</P>
</TEXT>
