<HEADLINE> First Rotating Gamma-Ray Stereotaxic Instrument Developed in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have
developed the world's first head-rotating gamma-ray stereotaxic
instrument and it will be China's first large advanced medical
instrument to be exported to the United States.
</P>
<P>
The XGD head-rotating instrument is jointly produced by
the Shenzhen Aowo International Science and Technology Development
Corporation and the Changzhou Machine Tool Factory.
</P>
<P>
An expert here said the newly developed instrument is superior
to the static ones in focusing gamma-ray on focus of infection
through skins and destroying the pathological tissue, as the
static ones sometimes may injure the healthy tissue.
</P>
<P>
The world's first static gamma-ray stereotaxic instrument was
invented by a Swedish scientist in 1968 and the instruments are
widely applied in "surgeries without wounds."
</P>
<P>
For instance, cerebral operations no longer need a craniotomy
and would not bleed with the help of gamma-ray instruments.
</P>
<P>
So far, the Changzhou factory has signed a 10-year agreement
with the Shenzhen company to produce the head-rotating gamma-ray
instrument in quantities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
