cities, including Beijing, Shanghai, and Tianjin, has been allowed
to open to the overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Wang suggested that local developers can make use of the
existing office buildings, warehouses, workshops, land, equipment,
and human resources as the investment in the cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Tianjin Municipal Foreign Trade Corporation and the
Japanese retailing giant Daiei Corporation has jointly launched
chain supermarkets in the city, which generated sales of over 60
million yuan (7.23 million US dollars) in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The Tianjin Foreign Trade Foodstuff Corporation cooperated with
China Resources Co. registered in Hongkong in establishing 11
chain stores in the city.
</P>
<P>
Local foreign trade companies are also cooperating with Daiei
in constructing large-scale food processing centers.
</P>
<P>
