<HEADLINE> U.N. Chief Shocked at Chiapas Massacre </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 24 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary General
Kofi Annan was deeply shocked to learn of Monday's massacre in
Mexico's Chiapas State, his spokesman said today.
</P>
<P>
The Secretary General "strongly condemns this odious crime, as
he does all acts of terrorism, and supports President Zedillo's
efforts to bring the perpetrators to justice", the spokesman told
reporters at a briefing.
</P>
<P>
Gunmen killed at least 46 defenseless peasants in a village of
Chiapas, Southern Mexico, leaving another 25 wounded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
