<DOCNO> XIE19971225.0203 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Financial Compensation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
announced the approval of 350 million U.S. dollars as the
financial compensation reconstruction assistance for Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The balance of payments loan will support Thailand's
comprehensive program to restructure its financial sector. The
structural measures supported by the loan will help restore
confidence in Thailand's ailing financial sector. The emphasis of
the loan is on streamlining the finance company subsector by
supporting the orderly exit of non-viable strengthening the
existing regulatory and supervisory framework, creating better
incentives for creditors, depositors, and debtors.
</P>
<P>
The program is designed to complement the International
Monetary Fund-supported macroeconomic stabilization package agreed
to by the Thai government.
</P>
<P>
The Single Currency Loan (SCL) will be repayable in 15 years
including a 3-year grace period and will be at the World Bank's
standard fixed US dollar SCL interest rate. 
</P>
</TEXT>
