<HEADLINE> U.S. to Add 2.4 Million More People in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 24 (Xinhua) The Census Bureau of the
United States has projected that there will be 268,921,733 people
living in the nation by January 1, 1998, 2.4 million more than the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
The Census Bureau predicted 3.9 million births, 2.3 million
deaths and 867,600 people returning or immigrating to the United
States in 1997, an Associated Press report said today.
</P>
<P>
The calculations represent an 8.1 percent increase from an
April 1990 census.
</P>
<P>
Census Bureau has found that the level of births has been
declining in the U.S. since 1990, but the number of deaths
increased in the past year.
</P>
<P>
The bureau predicted the country's population will grow by 2.3
million in the next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
