<HEADLINE> World Bank Okays Loans for Two Latin American Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
announced the approval of two loans totaling 31.4 million U.S.
dollars for Guatemala and Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
First loan of 15.7 million dollars equivalent will be used for
Guatemala's Integrated Financial Management Project II.
</P>
<P>
This project, with a total cost of some 18 million dollars,
expands reforms initiated under the current Financial Management
Program, also financed by the World Bank, that are increasing the
efficiency and transparency of the public sector and improving the
delivery of public services.
</P>
<P>
Second loan of 15.7 million dollars is provided for Venezuela's
Supreme Court Strengthening Project.
</P>
<P>
This project will begin to improve the performance of the
Supreme Court in terms of transparency, efficiency of
administration and case management as well as timeliness of
decisions, through development of new work methods, attitudes and
behaviors that would have a demonstration effect in leading
further judicial reform. 
</P>
</TEXT>
