<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves 2 Projects for Bosnia-Herzegovina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
announced the approval of two credits for Bosnia and Herzegovina
totaling 27 million U.S. dollars equivalent.
</P>
<P>
The first credit of some 10 million dollars will support the
reconstruction of the natural gas system of Sarajevo while the
second credit of some 17 million dollars will be provided to
support basic reconstruction investments in agriculture, housing,
water supply and electric power sectors in the Republika Srpska.
</P>
<P>
The emergency natural gas system reconstruction project is a 44
million dollar project. In addition to the World Bank credit, the
balance of 34 million dollars will be financed by other donors,
and about 22 million dollars have already been committed.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the second project is about 65 million
dollars. Apart from the World Bank credit, cofinancing and
parallel financing for 35 million dollars has already been offered
by other donors, including the European Union, the International
Fund for Agricultural Development and other European countries.
</P>
<P>
Both credits will be on standard terms of the International
Development Association, the World Bank's concessionary lending
arm for developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
