<DOCNO> XIE19971225.0212 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 59 Civilians Massacred in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Fifty-nine civilians were
massacred from Tuesday night till this morning in attacks
attributed to armed Islamic groups against two villages near the
capital Algiers, said reports from Algeria.
</P>
<P>
The new massacres brought the number of people killed since
Sunday to more than 100, as the Muslim fasting month of Ramadan is
only a few days away, said the reports.
</P>
<P>
Reports quoted Algerian security forces as saying that 48
villagers were killed at Sidi Lantri and M'ghila in the region of
Tiaret near Algiers, while 11 others were killed at Bainem, a
forest adjacent to the capital.
</P>
<P>
Muslim extremists usually consider Ramadan as a period for
waging the holy war. 
</P>
</TEXT>
