asked the Zimbabwean authorities to extradite two of its
countrymen who have murdered a British couple.
</P>
<P>
Virgilio Ferrao, governor of Tete Province said today that
they were negotiating with the Zimbabwean authorities which
detained the two men Monday.
</P>
<P>
He said that he wished the murderers could be sent back to
Mozambique within days.
</P>
<P>
The two men, with another man, were involved in a robbery and
killings of Andre and Caroline Macgown, a British couple, on the
high way in Tete Province on April 13.
</P>
<P>
The three were sentenced to 24 years in jail respectively in
October but 10 days ago they broke away from the jail with guns
with the help believed to be from the prison guards.
</P>
<P>
Two of the three fled to Zimbabwe and were detained by
Zimbabwean authorities and the other fugitive is also believed to
be in Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
It is said that the British embassy in Maputo is also pressing
the government to investigate the incident.
</P>
<P>
Mozambique and Zimbabwe have no agreement over criminal
extradition, but the two governments have been cooperating well
on the matter. 
