<HEADLINE> Clinton Expresses Outrage at Mexico Massacre </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 24 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
today expressed outrage at a massacre in Mexico in which 45
civilians were slaughtered and dozens more were wounded.
</P>
<P>
"He condemned the attack as a violation of the most basic human
values, and, on behalf of the American people, extends condolences
to the families of the victims," spokesman Mike McCurry said in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
"The president supports President (Ernesto) Zedillo's swift
action to investigate this appalling act and bring the
perpetrators to justice," he said.
</P>
<P>
"The president also strongly supports President Zedillo's call
for a redoubling of efforts to achieve peace in Chiapas through
political dialogue and reconciliation," he added.
</P>
<P>
Monday's attack by paramilitary gunmen occurred at a refugee
camp in Chiapas. Thirty-nine of the victims were women and
children, who had fled violence in other parts of the state.
</P>
</TEXT>
