<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Declares Northern Guam Disaster Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 24 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
today declared northern Guam, which was hit by Typhoon Paka last
week, a major disaster area, making residents there eligible for
federal aid.
</P>
<P>
The storm struck the islands on December 16 with torrential
rains and high wind and brought up tidal surges. Dozens of
residents were reported injured in the storm which destroyed many
houses and uprooted trees.
</P>
<P>
Governor Carl Guiterrez put the damage by the typhoon, one of
the worst in history, at 200 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Clinton's declaration opened the way for federal relief
including low-interest loans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
